        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 5:45AM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>Areas of fog, dense in some locations, has developed across
northern portions of the Piedmont this morning. The fog will
reduce visibilities to below one half mile or less at times.
Visibilities will start to improve between 8 and 9 am.

Motorists should be alert for sudden changes in visibility due to
the fog. Drive at reduced speeds...watch for children at school
bus stops...and use low beam headlights only.
</description>
